title: Dean Edell Medical Show 2009.01.14
description:
This is a full episode of Dr. Dean Edell's syndicated radio program, which airs on 136 stations across the United States. This episode aired on January 14, 2009.

In this episode, Dr. Edell tells us about a scientific study of human reactions to bad jokes, the new Pope's "holy war" on sightings of the Virgin Mary, the tenuous relationship between hallucinations and caffeine use, nationwide levels of caffeine use, shares the results of studies on the effectiveness of certain herbal medications (Black Cohosh, Wild Yams, Primrose Oil, Ginseng), and reveals the results of a study involving doctor-patient decisions regarding the breaking of negative prognoses.

He answers questions on goosebumps, allergic reactions to sweat, a vibrating exercise plate, unexplained pain after surgery, the Atkins Diet,and the use of a pesiri to avoid surgery on the uterus.
